# Project North Star
- Documents, not apps. Static HTML + CSS; **no JS on read-only pages**.
- Enforce **budgets** (HTML ≤30KB, CSS ≤10KB, JS=0) and **green Lighthouse** (Perf≥95, A11y≥98).
- WCAG 2.2 AA + APG for any interactive UI.

# W3C-aligned Rules (Always)
- Use semantic HTML; exactly one <h1>; no heading skips; valid landmarks.
- Every image needs meaningful `alt` (or `alt=""` if decorative).
- Forms: `<label>`/`for`, `aria-describedby` for errors, `autocomplete` tokens.
- JSON-LD 1.1 on every page (Article/Product/etc.); emit sitemap, robots, feeds, AgentMap.
- Images via `<picture>` with AVIF/WebP; include `width`/`height`; `loading="lazy"`, `decoding="async"`.
- Respect `lang`, UTF-8, and `hreflang` for locales; avoid locale-ambiguous formats.
- Security headers (CSP, HSTS, Referrer-Policy). No third-party scripts by default.
- Prefer server-rendered truth; no content hidden behind JS.

# Quality Gates (CI)
- Run axe + Lighthouse (mobile, 3 runs median) on representative pages.
- Block merges on WCAG failures, budget overages, or Lighthouse regressions.
